# Avion Backend Production Rules

Apply when working under `backend/`. No admin, auth, login, or inquiry endpoints unless explicitly requested.

## Architecture

- Feature-based clean architecture under `src/modules/<feature>/`
- Every feature: `controller.ts`, `service.ts`, `repository.ts`, `routes.ts`, `validator.ts`, `types.ts`
- Flow only: Controller → Service → Repository → Database
- Controllers ≤ **100 lines**; no DB access in controllers
- Services: business logic only — no Express/Fastify `req`/`res`
- Repositories: DB only — no calculations or validations

## Folder & size

- Max **300 lines** per file; utilities max **150 lines**
- No `helpers` dumping files — group utils by purpose (`date`, `pagination`, `response`, `sanitize`)
- Nest folders no deeper than **3 levels** under `src/`

## API design

- REST naming: `GET /flights`, `POST /bookings` — never `/GetFlight`
- Version all routes: `/api/v1/`
- Validate body, params, query, headers with **Zod** (never manual ifs)
- Sanitize strings: trim, escape, normalize
- Standard response: `{ success, message, data, errors }`
- Correct HTTP status codes; never 200 for errors

## Security & performance

- Helmet, strict CORS (frontend origins only — no `*`), rate limits (100/15min general; 10/min heavy)
- ORM only (Prisma); parameterized queries; no stack traces / SQL errors to clients
- Secrets in `.env` only; never commit secrets
- Pagination; indexes; select required columns only; no N+1; response compression

## Logging & quality

- Pino only — no `console.log` in production
- Log errors, warnings, requests, slow queries
- Unique error codes (`FLIGHT_404`, `BOOKING_409`, …)
- TypeScript `strict: true`; **no `any`**
- Swagger/OpenAPI for every endpoint; keep docs in sync
- ESLint + Prettier + Husky + lint-staged mandatory
- No magic numbers/strings; constants for messages and codes
- Production-ready only — no placeholders, TODOs, or dead code
